lity or justice. Kaufman demonstrates that capital trials ultimately depend on performance and politics, resulting in the enactment of deep biases and utter capriciousness. American Roulette contends that the liberal, democratic ideals of criminal punishment cannot be enacted in the current criminal justice system, even under the most controlled circumstances.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aCapital punishmentzUnited States. 0aCriminal justice, Administration ofxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aSentences (Criminal procedure)zUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh  aaggravating circumstances.  aamerican justice.  acapital defendants.  acapital jurors.  acapital punishment.  acapital sentencing.  acapital trials.  acourt cases.  acourtrooms.  acriminal justice.  acriminal punishment.  acriminal.  acriminology.  adeath penalty.  adeath row.  aethics.  aethnography.  ahomicide.  ajurors.  ajustice system.  ajustice.  alegal system.  amercy.  amorality.  amourning.  apolitics.  apoverty.  apsychological experts.  arace.  aracism.  asentencing.  asocial science.  asupreme court.  atrials.  avictim impact statement.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520975507zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40